autoConfigurator.files.description:
List of files (with content) to ensure exist in the workspace root or subfolders. Example usage:

  "autoConfigurator.files": [
    {
      "path": ".csharpierrc",
      "content": "{\"printWidth\": 120}",
      "rules": [
        { "type": "fileExistsGlob", "value": "**/*.csproj" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "path": ".gitignore",
      "content": "\\n.csharpierrc",
      "append": true,
      "rules": [
        { "type": "fileExistsGlob", "value": ".csharpierrc" }
      ]
    }
  ]

Each object should have a 'path' (relative file path, can include folders), optional 'content' (string to write if the file is created or appended), optional 'append' (if true, append content), and optional 'rules' (array of rule objects). If 'rules' is omitted, the file is always created/appended if missing. Supported rule types: 'fileNotExists', 'envVarSet', 'fileExistsGlob', 'folderExists', 'settingEquals', 'fileContains', 'workspaceName'. No files are created unless you specify them here.
